Lozotaenia costinotana is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from Maine, Manitoba, Minnesota and Quebec.
The wingspan is 18â€“23 mm. The forewings are grey white, but whitest along the costa and outer margin. There is a pattern of blackish-brown transverse lines, as well as a black costal spot. The hindwings are white, the inner margin and apical area with brownish-black scales. Adults have been recorded on wing from July to August.